parts.text:
**Asian**

**Soups:**
* Tom Yum (Thai sour and spicy soup)
* Pho (Vietnamese beef noodle soup)
* Ramen (Japanese noodle soup with various toppings)
* Tonkotsu Ramen (Japanese pork bone broth noodle soup)
* Miso Shiru (Japanese soybean paste soup)
* Laksa (Malaysian or Singaporean coconut milk noodle soup)
* Congee (Chinese rice porridge with various toppings)

**Stews:**
* Massaman Curry (Thai beef curry stew)
* Shabu-Shabu (Japanese hot pot stew)
* Sukiyaki (Japanese beef stew with various vegetables)
* Mapo Tofu (Chinese spicy tofu stew)

**Hot Drinks:**
* Matcha (Japanese green tea powder)
* Jasmine Tea (Chinese fragrant tea)
* Bubble Tea (Taiwanese tea with tapioca pearls)
* Vietnamese Egg Coffee (coffee with egg yolks and condensed milk)
* Dalgona Coffee (South Korean whipped coffee)

**Mediterranean**

**Soups:**
* Gazpacho (Spanish cold tomato soup)
* Avgolemono (Greek lemon-egg soup)
* Bouillabaisse (French seafood soup)
* Ribollita (Italian Tuscan bread and bean soup)

**Stews:**
* Tagine (North African stew with various meats and vegetables)
* Paella (Spanish rice dish with seafood and vegetables)
* Moussaka (Greek eggplant and potato casserole)
* Ratatouille (French vegetable stew)

**Hot Drinks:**
* Turkish Coffee (strong, thick coffee brewed in a traditional cezve)
* Salep (Turkish hot drink made from orchid root powder)
* Sahleb (Egyptian hot drink made from rice and cinnamon)
* Mint Tea (Moroccan tea infused with fresh mint leaves)
* Masala Chai (Indian tea with spices and milk)
